Improve Listing Accessibility with Alt Text In Carousel Images

Ensure your AppExchange listings are accessible and search-engine friendly by adding descriptive alt text to all carousel images. Alt text helps low-vision users understand image content and can improve your listing's search engine rankings.

Who: To edit listings in the AppExchange Partner Console, you must have the Manage Listings permission in the Salesforce Partner Community.

Why: Salesforce is committed to making our enterprise applications accessible to all individuals, including users working with assistive devices, such as screen readers. Partners are encouraged to do the same.

Alt text is also beneficial for search engine optimization (SEO). Google and other third-party search engines index alt text to understand what images depict. This can enhance how search engines comprehend your listing and lead to higher search rankings.

The carousel on an AppExchange listing contains up to 15 images and videos. It’s the largest section on the listing page and the biggest opportunity to improve a listing’s accessibility and SEO. Alt text for carousel images is now required for new listings and highly recommended for existing listings.

How: To add alt text to a carousel image, edit your listing in the AppExchange Partner Console. Go to Include Visuals (1) and enter alt text (2) for each carousel image. Describe each image in one sentence so that individuals who use screen readers can perceive what the image depicts.
title: Improving AppExchange Listings with Alt Text
